.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS.AUDIOLEVEL" "3JS" "August 15, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats.audioLevel \- RTCInboundRtpStreamStats:
audioLevel property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]audioLevel\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[R] dictionary indicates the audio level
of the received (remote) track.
.PP
The \f[CR]audioLevel\f[R] is averaged over some small interval, using
the algorithm described under \f[CR]totalAudioEnergy\f[R].
The interval used is implementation dependent.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The value is undefined for video streams.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A real number.
.PP
The value is between 0..1 (linear), where 1.0 represents 0 dBov (\c
.UR https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DBFS
decibels relative to full scale (DBFS)
.UE \c
), 0 represents silence, and 0.5 represents approximately 6 dB SPL
change in the \c
.UR https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sound_pressure#Sound_pressure_level
sound pressure level
.UE \c
\ from 0 dBov.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]RTCAudioSourceStats.audioLevel\f[R] for audio levels of local
tracks (that are being sent)
